# Full Stack Engineer – Expected Deliverables & Professional Expectations

## Purpose

This document defines the expected deliverables, behaviors, engineering practices, and professional standards for Full Stack Engineers participating in modern software delivery initiatives.

The objective is to establish a common framework for execution across Spec-Driven Development (SDD), MVP delivery, Agile practices, AI-assisted engineering, quality assurance, and continuous improvement.

---

# Core Principle

A Full Stack Engineer is expected to deliver business capabilities from concept to production-ready MVPs.

The expectation extends beyond coding and includes:

- Requirements understanding
- Solution design
- Development
- Testing
- Documentation
- Deployment readiness
- Knowledge sharing
- Continuous improvement

Success is measured by business value delivered with quality, speed, accountability, and collaboration.

---

# Technical Deliverables

| Category | Deliverable | Description |
|-----------|-------------|-------------|
| Requirements Analysis | Technical Analysis | Interpretation of business requirements, assumptions, dependencies, and risks |
| Specification Refinement | Technical Specification | Conversion of functional requirements into technical implementation details |
| Architecture | Solution Design | Architecture diagrams, workflows, integrations, and component definitions |
| Frontend Development | User Interface | Functional and reusable frontend components following established standards |
| Backend Development | Services & APIs | Business logic, APIs, integrations, validation, and error handling |
| Data Design | Data Model | Database schemas, entities, relationships, and persistence strategy |
| Workflow Design | Process Orchestration | Business process flows and state management |
| Cloud Integration | Platform Components | Integration with approved cloud services and enterprise platforms |
| Security | Security Controls | Authentication, authorization, validation, and secure coding practices |
| Testing | Automated Validation | Unit, Integration, and End-to-End testing |
| Documentation | Technical Documentation | Installation, configuration, architecture, and operational documentation |
| Delivery | MVP Demonstration | Demonstrable functionality aligned with business requirements |
| Knowledge Transfer | Handover | Walkthroughs, demos, and operational knowledge sharing |

